GUSMANN, Harry (28, painter), end 



GUSMANN, Elizabeth; 

uttering counterfeit coin; possessing counterfeit coin, with intent to utter same.

Dr. WADE, house surgeon, Great Northern Hospital. On March 21 at about 6.30 p.m. I saw deceased in the hospital; he was unconscious. An operation was performed that night, but he never recovered con
sciousness, dying at 3.30 on Sunday morning. I made a post
mortem and found the body was well nourished, very healthy, age about 30;

